<A HREF="/web/20000711075713/http://www.forbes.com/tool/toolbox/billnew/00"><B>Billionaires Worldwide 2000</B></A>&nbsp;(Flash required)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<A HREF="/web/20000711075713/http://www.forbes.com/tool/toolbox/billnew/00/noflash.htm"><B>Enter without Flash</B></A><P>
<B>Specials: <A HREF="/web/20000711075713/http://www.forbes.com/tool/toolbox/billnew/00/techbill.htm">Technology Billionaires</A>&nbsp;&&nbsp;<A HREF="/web/20000711075713/http://www.forbes.com/tool/toolbox/billnew/00/women.htm">The World's Wealthiest Women 
</A></B><P>
<FONT SIZE="+0"><B>Billionaires</B></FONT> 
<I>By Lisa DiCarlo</I>
<BR>
<FONT SIZE="+0"><B>W</B></FONT>hat a roller coaster of a year! Gates is still the richest but his fortune was sliced by a third. Poor guy. Wall Street changed its tune about dot-coms--turns out profits do matter--and many millions were lost in the process. Now it's all about global expansion, as companies look to seed fertile, particularly technology-related, markets outside U.S. borders.<P>
This year's database contains 308 billionaires totaling $1.27 trillion in
wealth. Only the top 51 of the richest working Americans are listed. (We will publish the full American list in September in the annual <a href="/web/20000711075713/http://www.forbes.com/tool/toolbox/rich400/" target = "blank">Forbes 400</a>.) Notice a continent missing? No one from Antartica has ever made the list. 
