<P>
<FONT SIZE="-1" FACE="verdana,geneva,helvetica">For a few weeks, Ellison and Gates competed for the title of world's richest person. Amazing, since Ellison's worth last year was one tenth of Gates'. Son's big jump was due partly to Softbanks's divestiture of "not-coms" and a new, exclusive focus on Internet pure plays. As for Kirch, looks like his 45% purchase of pay TV company Premiere and restructuring of his media holdings has paid off quite nicely.</FONT><P>
